@startuml current_005_render_flow
title UC Life Sim — render seam (Pixi snapshot vs. DOM HUD)

' Architectural point: the render layer has TWO ways to read ECS state.
' Visual marks (worldspace) take per-frame snapshots; DOM HUD subscribes
' via koota/react. This diagram shows only that contrast — sub-modules
' (sprite, space, portrait, particles) are noted, not drawn.

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Inter, sans-serif"
skinparam linetype ortho
left to right direction

[koota World\n(active scene)] as ECS

package "render/ (worldspace, pixi)" as R #e9f3ff {
  [Game.tsx\nuseEffect RAF\n→ build GroundSnapshot] as GAME
  [PixiGroundRenderer\n(+ PixiSpaceRenderer / Tactical)] as RENDER
}

package "ui/ (DOM, React + zustand)" as U #e9f3ff {
  [Hud / StatusPanel /\nModals / SpaceView / …] as HUD
}

ECS  --> GAME    : world.query() each frame
GAME --> RENDER  : update(snap, cam)
ECS  --> HUD     : useQuery / useTrait\n(via koota/react)

note bottom of GAME
  Background pointerdown on the host
  div sets MoveTarget on IsPlayer.
  NPC + interactable Pixi nodes carry
  their own pointerdown handlers
  (eventMode='static') — no O(N) hit
  scan on click.
end note

note bottom of RENDER
  Sub-modules referenced from here:
   - render/sprite     LPC composer
                       (appearanceToLpc, animTick)
   - render/space      PixiSpaceRenderer,
                       PixiTacticalRenderer, particles
   - render/portrait   FC pregmod port
                       (see 006)
  These are implementation detail of
  the renderer, not part of the seam.
end note

note top of HUD
  HUD is the legitimate koota/react
  bridge — useQuery / useTrait keeps
  React rendering pure-read of ECS.
end note

@enduml
